39
00:01:37,247 --> 00:01:39,616
Not just about this social media war.

40
00:01:39,616 --> 00:01:43,272
The whole controversy was driven by hateful politics.

41
00:01:43,272 --> 00:01:46,770
A geopolitical agenda which led to all of this.

42
00:01:46,770 --> 00:01:48,940
Let's understand it in today's video.

43
00:01:56,845 --> 00:01:58,260
One thing you all would know is that

44
00:01:58,260 --> 00:02:00,379
Maldives is a small country.

45
00:02:00,379 --> 00:02:04,384
The total population of this country 
is only around 500,000 people.

46
00:02:04,384 --> 00:02:06,336
This country is made up of numerous islands.

47
00:02:06,336 --> 00:02:08,209
In fact, there are more than 1,000 islands.

48
00:02:08,209 --> 00:02:10,101
But out of these 1,000 islands,

49
00:02:10,101 --> 00:02:12,901
only about 200 are inhabited.

50
00:02:12,901 --> 00:02:14,530
Where humans live.

51
00:02:14,530 --> 00:02:15,577
And out of these 200,

52
00:02:15,577 --> 00:02:18,661
more than 150 islands are resort islands.

53
00:02:18,661 --> 00:02:21,026
They have been sold to private companies.

54
00:02:21,026 --> 00:02:23,707
And those companies have their private resorts on it.

55
00:02:27,841 --> 00:02:31,009
Obviously, the country depends heavily on tourism.

56
00:02:31,009 --> 00:02:34,756
28% of Maldives' GDP depends on tourism.

57
00:02:34,756 --> 00:02:38,130
And 90% of the tax revenue for the government,

58
00:02:38,130 --> 00:02:41,473
comes from import duties and tourism-related taxes.

59
00:02:41,473 --> 00:02:43,042
And an interesting fact is that

60
00:02:43,042 --> 00:02:44,696
India is the number one country

61
00:02:44,696 --> 00:02:47,382
based on the number of tourists visiting Maldives.

62
00:02:47,382 --> 00:02:51,393
In 2023, more than 200,000 Indian tourists went to Maldives.

63
00:02:51,393 --> 00:02:55,103
In total, approx 1.75 million tourists 
went to Maldives this year.

64
00:02:55,103 --> 00:02:57,669
So you can imagine a country with a population of 500,000,

65
00:02:57,669 --> 00:03:00,261
hosting more than 1.7 million tourists in a year.

66
00:03:00,261 --> 00:03:01,876
But the relationship between India and Maldives

67
00:03:01,876 --> 00:03:04,133
is much deeper than that of tourism.

68
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:07,142
For years, India and Maldives have been strategic allies

69
00:03:07,142 --> 00:03:10,208
and there has been military cooperation between the two too.

70
00:03:10,208 --> 00:03:13,577
India has played a special role in initiatives like SAGAR.

71
00:03:13,577 --> 00:03:14,886
SAGAR stands for

72
00:03:14,886 --> 00:03:16,857
Security and Growth for All in the Region.

73
00:03:16,857 --> 00:03:20,206
Around 2008, India launched its Neighbourhood First Policy,

74
00:03:20,206 --> 00:03:22,301
and improved relations with Sri Lanka, Maldives,

75
00:03:22,301 --> 00:03:24,779
Nepal, Afghanistan, Bangladesh,

76
00:03:24,779 --> 00:03:26,930
Pakistan, and Myanmar.

77
00:03:26,930 --> 00:03:30,068
About 77 Indian military officers and soldiers

78
00:03:30,068 --> 00:03:32,027
are present on the Maldives islands

79
00:03:32,027 --> 00:03:35,948
additionally, two Dhruv Advanced Light Helicopters

80
00:03:35,948 --> 00:03:40,022
were donated by India to the Maldives in 2010 and 2015.

81
00:03:40,022 --> 00:03:43,084
There are many reasons behind this 
military presence and helicopter donation.

82
00:03:43,084 --> 00:03:45,001
Such as helping during natural calamities,

83
00:03:45,001 --> 00:03:46,877
conducting search and rescue operations,

84
00:03:46,877 --> 00:03:50,288
airlifting medical patients between islands.

85
00:03:50,288 --> 00:03:53,035
But apart from this, India's warships patrol the

86
00:03:53,035 --> 00:03:56,121
exclusive economic zone of the Maldives too.

87
00:03:56,121 --> 00:03:58,227
This is the sea area surrounding Maldives

88
00:03:58,227 --> 00:04:01,805
where illegal activity is prevented.

89
00:04:01,805 --> 00:04:03,140
Basically, to prevent terrorism.

90
00:04:03,140 --> 00:04:06,626
Maldives had requested India to do this.

91
00:04:06,626 --> 00:04:08,688
In 2009, when the Maldivian government

92
00:04:08,688 --> 00:04:12,031
were concerned about potential 
terrorist attacks in their country,

93
00:04:12,031 --> 00:04:14,012
they had asked India for help

94
00:04:14,012 --> 00:04:17,423
because they did not have the capabilities 
in terms of military assets and surveillance.

95
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:20,370
But this help and India's military presence

96
00:04:20,370 --> 00:04:25,236
has become a major issue of controversy 
in Maldives' internal politics for the last few years.

97
00:04:25,236 --> 00:04:28,463
Some political parties in Maldives completely oppose this

98
00:04:28,463 --> 00:04:31,176
and want India to withdraw its military.

99
00:04:31,176 --> 00:04:34,576
In fact, Maldives' current President, Mohamed Muizzu

100
00:04:34,576 --> 00:04:37,813
and his political party, People's National Congress,

101
00:04:37,813 --> 00:04:39,641
used this issue during their election campaign

102
00:04:39,641 --> 00:04:41,071
and came to power.

103
00:04:41,071 --> 00:04:43,118
The issue of "India Out."

104
00:04:43,118 --> 00:04:44,411
To understand this better,

105
00:04:44,411 --> 00:04:46,991
we have to take a look at Maldives' internal politics.

106
00:04:46,991 --> 00:04:51,693
The thing is, the country was 
under dictatorship for 30 years.

107
00:04:51,693 --> 00:04:53,567
It was only in 2008

108
00:04:53,567 --> 00:04:56,291
that a new constitution was adopted

109
00:04:56,291 --> 00:04:59,950
and a multi-party democracy system 
was established in their country.

110
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:02,432
The elections that were conducted in 2008

111
00:05:02,432 --> 00:05:07,816
was won by the Maldivian 
Democratic Party or MDP in short

112
00:05:07,816 --> 00:05:10,970
and their new President was Mohamed Nasheed.

113
00:05:10,970 --> 00:05:14,747
He was a successful president for the first 4 years of his term.

114
00:05:14,747 --> 00:05:17,154
He spread awareness on climate change issues,

115
00:05:17,154 --> 00:05:20,359
pledged to make Maldives carbon neutral

116
00:05:20,359 --> 00:05:22,780
and his foreign policy was India First.

117
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:26,434
During his term, India and Maldives became close allies.

118
00:05:26,434 --> 00:05:28,971
And as I said, in 2009, on his request,

119
00:05:28,971 --> 00:05:31,913
India donated military equipment to Maldives.

120
00:05:31,913 --> 00:05:35,631
But in 2012, a political crisis broke out in Maldives.

121
00:05:35,631 --> 00:05:38,399
And the next year, in 2013, 
when elections took place,

122
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:40,151
