00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:36,118
Leaked documents suggest that

265
00:11:36,118 --> 00:11:37,409
according to this agreement,

266
00:11:37,409 --> 00:11:39,917
the Indian military could stay here for decades

267
00:11:39,917 --> 00:11:43,241
and they would have the exclusive rights to this facility.

268
00:11:43,735 --> 00:11:46,957
Many Maldivian citizens were 
genuinely upset after hearing this.

269
00:11:46,957 --> 00:11:50,283
Even those who were not 
supporting the India Out campaign,

270
00:11:50,283 --> 00:11:52,575
started supporting the opposition.

271
00:11:52,575 --> 00:11:56,499
And because of this, when the next 
elections were conducted in 2023,

272
00:11:56,499 --> 00:11:58,347
the governing party changed again,

273
00:11:58,347 --> 00:12:01,444
and the PPM party that was the opposition,

274
00:12:01,444 --> 00:12:03,269
came back into power.

275
00:12:03,269 --> 00:12:05,030
This time, this PPM party

276
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:08,635
formed an alliance with PNC party to be in power.

277
00:12:08,635 --> 00:12:10,586
And the latest President of Maldives,

278
00:12:10,586 --> 00:12:11,650
Mohamed Muizzu,

279
00:12:11,650 --> 00:12:14,706
was the candidate of this right-wing party, PNC.

280
00:12:14,706 --> 00:12:17,363
This happened on 30th September, 2023.

281
00:12:17,363 --> 00:12:22,523
This political party, which focused on the 
India Out issue during their election campaign

282
00:12:22,523 --> 00:12:24,182
is in power today.

283
00:12:24,182 --> 00:12:25,764
It is also worth noting that

284
00:12:25,764 --> 00:12:29,802
had the previous MDP government been more transparent

285
00:12:29,802 --> 00:12:32,898
and had not kept the agreements so confidential,

286
00:12:32,898 --> 00:12:35,216
then perhaps the India Out sentiment

287
00:12:35,216 --> 00:12:36,723
would not have gained so much traction.

288
00:12:36,723 --> 00:12:38,979
And perhaps, they could have remained in power.

289
00:12:38,979 --> 00:12:41,954
But now, since this PPM party came into power,

290
00:12:41,954 --> 00:12:48,387
they took this India Out issue 
even more seriously than last time.

291
00:12:48,387 --> 00:12:50,385
Their new president Mohamed Muizzu,

292
00:12:50,385 --> 00:12:54,580
openly stated, four days after winning the election

293
00:12:54,580 --> 00:12:57,101
that Indian forces in Maldives

294
00:12:57,101 --> 00:12:58,866
will have to leave the country.

295
00:12:58,866 --> 00:13:01,767
On 17th November 2023, 
he became the President officially,

296
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:03,486
and only a week later,

297
00:13:03,486 --> 00:13:04,746
on 23rd November,

298
00:13:04,746 --> 00:13:07,639
he met Indian Union Minister Kiren Rijiju.

299
00:13:07,639 --> 00:13:09,722
He repeated the same points in the meeting

300
00:13:09,722 --> 00:13:13,470
that India withdraw its military personnel from Maldives.

301
00:13:13,470 --> 00:13:16,113
And it was only a month and a half later

302
00:13:16,113 --> 00:13:18,702
that the Muizzu's ministers

303
00:13:18,702 --> 00:13:20,979
openly started insulting PM Modi and India

304
00:13:20,979 --> 00:13:23,339
on public platform.

305
00:13:23,339 --> 00:13:25,748
When this happened, the ex-Presidents of Maldives

306
00:13:25,748 --> 00:13:27,682
and the MDP party,

307
00:13:27,682 --> 00:13:32,301
obviously, stood up in favour of India.

308
00:13:32,301 --> 00:13:34,385
Mohamed Nasheed and Ibrahim Mohamed Solih

309
00:13:34,385 --> 00:13:38,542
both condemned this hateful language against India.

310
00:13:38,542 --> 00:13:40,668
Now that you know these, you can understand

311
00:13:40,668 --> 00:13:43,636
that it was never about Lakshadweep.

312
00:13:43,636 --> 00:13:47,498
This was entirely about Maldives' internal politics.

313
00:13:47,498 --> 00:13:49,568
This India Out sentiment

314
00:13:49,568 --> 00:13:52,343
is a way for some Maldivian politicians

315
00:13:52,343 --> 00:13:53,946
to incite their citizens

316
00:13:53,946 --> 00:13:57,398
and to score more votes with their hateful speeches.

317
00:13:57,398 --> 00:14:01,195
In 2021, when the MDP government was in power 
and India Out slogans were raised,

318
00:14:01,195 --> 00:14:03,932
then one of the MDP ministers Ali Azim had said that

319
00:14:03,932 --> 00:14:06,163
this anti-India movement was

320
00:14:06,163 --> 00:14:08,689
happening because some people

321
00:14:08,689 --> 00:14:10,774
enjoy making hateful speeches.

322
00:14:10,774 --> 00:14:12,518
Today, this is a great example of how

323
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:17,424
hateful politics can be harmful to a country.

324
00:14:17,424 --> 00:14:19,768
You will find such politicians not only in Maldives

325
00:14:19,768 --> 00:14:21,703
but in every country in the world.

326
00:14:21,703 --> 00:14:25,261
They either spread hatred against a community,

327
00:14:25,261 --> 00:14:27,461
against a religion

328
00:14:27,461 --> 00:14:30,073
or against another country.

329
00:14:30,073 --> 00:14:32,013
What's unfortunate is that,

330
00:14:32,013 --> 00:14:36,202
many people get misled by such 
hateful speeches and the fear they create.

331
00:14:36,202 --> 00:14:38,441
If we look at the foreign policy of the new Maldivian government,

332
00:14:38,441 --> 00:14:41,491
it is once again leaning towards China.

333
00:14:41,491 --> 00:14:43,383
Maybe it's just a coincidence that

334
00:14:43,383 --> 00:14:46,573
this entire controversy started just a day before

335
00:14:46,573 --> 00:14:49,350
the Maldivian President's visit to China.

336
00:14:49,350 --> 00:14:52,557
His trip to China was from 8th to 12th January.

337
00:14:52,557 --> 00:14:53,846
The Chinese state-sponsored media

338
00:14:53,846 --> 00:14:55,418
praised this situation stating that

339
00:14:55,418 --> 00:15:00,636
"it demonstrates that Muizzu is treating 
India with a normal mindset

340
00:15:00,636 --> 00:15:03,596
and steering the relationship between Maldives and India

341
00:15:03,596 --> 00:15:05,807
to a normal state-state relationship."

342
00:15:05,807 --> 00:15:07,977
It is also historic that

343
00:15:07,977 --> 00:15:11,738
Muizzu chose China for his first foreign trip.

344
00:15:11,738 --> 00:15:14,470
All the Maldivian presidents before him,

345
00:15:14,470 --> 00:15:17,536
came to India on their first foreign trip.

346
00:15:17,536 --> 00:15:20,261
Just two days ago, on 10th January,

347
00:15:20,261 --> 00:15:22,052
after this controversy began,

348
00:15:22,052 --> 00:15:26,888
President Muizzu extended an 
invitation to Chinese tourists

349
00:15:26,888 --> 00:15:28,663
to visit Maldives.

350
00:15:28,663 --> 00:15:31,041
Since Indians started boycotting the country,

351
00:15:31,041 --> 00:15:34,803
he is openly inviting Chinese tourists to his country.

352
00:15:34,803 --> 00:15:37,744
So, the entire issue here 
is about Maldives' internal politics.

353
00:15:37,744 --> 00:15:39,726
The parties in favour of China

354
00:15:39,726 --> 00:15:41,834
versus the parties in favour of India.

355
00:15:41,834 --> 00:15:43,370
This also reveals that

356
00:15:43,370 --> 00:15:47,070
if the governing party changes once again
in Maldives in 4-5 years,

357
00:15:47,070 --> 00:15:49,339
and the pro-India party comes to power,

358
00:15:49,339 --> 00:15:51,921
then India's stance towards Maldives can change again.

